description.narrative: This activity (Support to Business Enabling Environment) is a component of Private Sector Development Programme in Malawi reported by FCDO, with a funding type of 'Multilateral organisation' and a budget of £1,774,399. This component benefits Malawi, and works in the following sector(s): Public sector policy and administrative management, Business Policy and Administration, Agricultural policy and administrative management, Industrial development, Mineral/mining policy and administrative management, Trade policy and administrative management, Trade facilitation. , with the following implementing partners: Coffey International Development, Deloitte, Deutsche Gesellschaft für Internationale Zusammenarbeit (GIZ), HM Revenue and Customs, Landell Mills, World Bank, The. The start date is 05-02-2013 and the end date is 31-12-2017.
